citeinfo.origin: California Office of Statewide Health Planning and Development
citeinfo.title: Licensed Healthcare Facilities, California, 2006

descript.abstract: This point shapefile represents healthcare facilities licensed by the State of California, Department of Health Services (DHS), as of1997. Facility address information is maintained and provided by the Office of Statewide Health Planning and Development (OSHPD). Facility types include hospitals, nursing homes, clinics, etc.
descript.purpose: This layer provides location information for mapping healthcare facilities in California.
descript.supplinf: Licensed healthcare facility address data are extracted from the the Automated Licensing Information and Report Tracking System (ALIRTS), an OSHPD information system. All address data are validated against a U.S. Postal Service address database and geocoded using ArcInfo Desktop 9.x against Tele Atlas (GDT) Dynamap/2000 reference data sets, v13, 14, 15.

The user will not seek to hold the State or the Department liable under any circumstances for any damages with respect to any claim by the user or any third party on account of or arising from the use of data or maps. The user will cite the Office of Statewide Health Planning and Development as the original source of the data, but will clearly denote cases where the original data have been updated, modified, or in any way altered from the original condition. There are no restrictions on distribution of the data by users. However, users are encouraged to refer others to the Office of Statewide Health Planning and Development to acquire the data, in case updated data become available.

attr.attrdef: Unique key identifying a licensed healthcare facility that reports data to the California Office of Statewide Health Planning and Development.

ZIP Code listed on facility license; five-digit ZIP Code only.

Healthcare facility contact phone number derived from utilization reports stored in ALIRTS.

Geocode match type code

Urbanized Area as defined by the U.S. Census Bureau (boolean)

Describes the category and type of control (ownership) of the healthcare facility licensee.

Facility is a teaching hospital. (boolean)

Address geocoding match score on scale of 0-100. Higher scores are generally better, but it will depend on which data was used to perform the geocode. Geocoding is the process of converting an address string into a map coordinate such as Latitude/Longitude.

Latitude, geographic projection, NAD83.
County FIPS Code.

Health Service Area [HSA] is a geographic area consisting of one or more contiguous counties, previously designated by the federal Department of Health and Human Services for health planning on a regional basis.
Service Planning Area [SPA] ia a geographic area designated by Los Angeles County, within the County, for healthcare planning purposes.
California Office of Emergency Services [OES] administrative region.
OSHPD Facilities Development Division [FDD] administrative region.
Identifies a Medical Service Study Area [MSSA].
Feature geometry.
Medical Service Study Areas are defined as either Urban, Rural, or Frontier based on established population criteria.
County name.
Simple census tract code.
State Senate District number.
Total number of licensed beds housed by the healthcare facility as reported by the Department of Health Services [CDHS].
Trauma Center Designation level of the hospital as reported by the California Emergency Medical Services Authority [EMSA].

dataIdInfo.idAbs: This point shapefile represents healthcare facilities licensed by the State of California, Department of Health Services (DHS), as of1997. Facility address information is maintained and provided by the Office of Statewide Health Planning and Development (OSHPD). Facility types include hospitals, nursing homes, clinics, etc. This layer is part of the Healthcare Atlas of California.
dataIdInfo.idPurp: This layer provides location information for mapping healthcare facilities in California.
dataIdInfo.idCredit: California Office of Statewide Health Planning and Development. (2013). Licensed Healthcare Facilities, California, 2006. California Office of Statewide Health Planning and Development. Available at: http://purl.stanford.edu/fv912rh6945.

dataIdInfo.suppInfo: Licensed healthcare facility address data are extracted from the the Automated Licensing Information and Report Tracking System (ALIRTS), an OSHPD information system. All address data are validated against a U.S. Postal Service address database and geocoded using ArcInfo Desktop 9.x against Tele Atlas (GDT) Dynamap/2000 reference data sets, v13, 14, 15.
dataIdInfo.envirDesc: Microsoft Windows 7 Version 6.1 (Build 7601) Service Pack 1; Esri ArcGIS 10.3.1.4959

prcStep.stepDesc: Updated from ALIRTS system. Copied facility name aliases from previous feature class. Reviewed and updated facility alias names. More Details: Created XY event from source table. Selected records with nonzero lat/long. Project from WGS84 to NAD83 geographic. Project from geographic to CA Teale Albers. Join current feature class to new feature class on OSHPDID and copy over alias names. Verify pre-existing alias names for facilities that were updated in ALIRTS since this was last done; fix as needed. Add new alias names for any facility still missing an alias name. Update metadata. Update into ArcSDE.
